metadata.name: TENDER Pass #652
metadata.description:
Tender is a curatorial platform and community that helps bring incredible works of generative art to discerning collectors.

Holding a TENDER Pass enables enriched benefits and experiences within the Tender ecosystem. Passholders expand their access to unique collaborations with extraordinary artists, indispensable collector tools, curatorial experiences, artwork insights, fine art prints, a thriving community, and more.

Tender is committed to stewarding the growth of generative art and amplifying the voices of artists and collectors across the entire lifecycle: from creation to collection to curation, and back again. Every Pass minted and resold directly enables Tender to continue creating the platform and experiences that serve this mission.

——

TENDER Pass features unique artwork by punevyr. While all Passes are special, a small number of randomly generated, rarified tokens will come with boosted benefits. If you have a piece with a dark background of any kind, you likely possess one of the following:

Bonus Pass
TENDER Passes with the special Bonus trait get 1 guaranteed reserve spot on all TENDER x Collab projects

Grail Pass
TENDER Passes with the special Grail trait get 2 free mints on all TENDER x Collab projects


New Passholders may access our Discord server that’s linked from our website.
For TENDER Pass benefits and up-to-date details, please visit tender.art/pass


Artwork created with p5.js

---

TENDER x punevyr
July 2022

metadata.name: Heat Death #846
metadata.description:
Heat Death is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at The Ever-Evolving World of Art, Art Basel Hong-Kong, 2022

It aims to produce variation and detail from minimal logic.

The source code uses p5.js and consists of around 180 lines of code. It has been left unminified for the interested viewer to learn more.

metadata.name: Memory Module #85
metadata.description:
Day by day, memories accumulate and shape our dreams, subconscious, ideals, and ultimately, the innermost self. 

This artwork is created by repeatedly drawing squares that are identical in size, with each one representing a memory. As new memories form, the older ones become obscured, fuzzy, or joined with others to form belief structures and intuitions. I hope that this work will remind you of someone, someplace, a song or a melody that’s important to you. 

Keyboard controls:
[S] Save the current view in live mode.
[1] to [8] Change resolution, 1.5K to 12K.
[G] Toggle paper texture.

URL params:
aspect: custom aspect ratio (?aspect=3).
res: custom resolution multiplier (?res=4).

Made with fractal math and p5js, Memory Module is the first in a 5-part generative art series about introspection. You can read more about the series here: https://elsifthen.github.io/

Created by elsif, 2022.07.

metadata.name: Alienpillars #80
metadata.description:
"A rare type of bug that supposedly arrived on a cargo ship is destroying crops on planet Uctumi, in the binary system of Extronium. A wide variety of very resistant subspecies has mutated and it is necessary to study and identify all of them to obtain a gen-activated pesticide that will work on all of their variations. The pest department of the Uctumi central government is working hard on it, and they say that these strange critters are probably related to similar species that inhabited the planet Earth of the Solar system a long time ago and have spread over the galaxy."

My second piece using the p5.js raymarcher I wrote. The drawing is made of circles and lines based on the 3D data. I wanted to try something hairy as it's easy to draw lines aligned to the surface normal with this method. I also used a shader for the frame and the glitchy/sketch features.

Features 

body color: green-red-purple-yellow-blue-black
body tone: dark-light
spots color: orange-green-blue-yellow-white
hair tips: yes-no
hair #1: short-medium-long
hair #2: short-medium-long
head size: small-medium-large
head shape: long-spherical-wide
glitchy mode: 10% chance
sketch mode: 9% chance

metadata.name: Arrows Between Emotions #61
metadata.description:
The project “Arrows Between Emotions” was formed with a concern to present this transformation in an artist and code developer, making the logic appear through precise and well-defined forms, but that the stage was really of emotions through freer curves involving aligned with accentuated movements in directions of straight or oblique ascents and even in more circular or decadent processes that are part of the journey of the wheel of life of art and the artist.


The process of the work involved the construction of a background to receive the shapes and colors. I used an algorithm that generated a distribution of noise across the screen, with its coloring related to the shapes in the search for a pleasant composition. Then came the objective forms, setting the stage, finally, for the flow of emotions through the agglutinated and dispersed curves soaked in colors in a game of shadow and light, presenting the depth and movement of the creation process and the orientation to which it takes. all the strength of this walk.

Press 's' key in live mode to save in png.

metadata.name: Valley of Empty Future #33
metadata.description:
*translated from drone swarm operator 51b13*
Preliminary analysis of the planet's atmosphere suggest an increased concentration of carbon monoxide, consistent with temperature readings.
No fauna or flora detected on immediate surface. Even though soil spectroscopy confirm presence of organic compounds, samples must be collected in order to have definitive results.

Scouts have confirmed, trough x-ray and radar imaging, sprawling areas of artificial environments. High density of buildings suggest an intricate and highly developed societal structure, with only it's tallest buildings piercing trough the meters deep silicate dust covering most of the area. It intrigues me why build so high, would these be religious monuments to be seen by all, for their exuberance? Immediately forwarding digital reconstruction of the -cities?- for Cosmic Sociologists to further speculate on their purposes.

////

On fullscreen view, press P to download a 1920*2560 PNG

Made in Cables.gl

metadata.name: Mount Doodle #180
metadata.description:
Tried my best to make every doodle aesthetically pleasing to the eyes.
However, just like nature, beauty often lies in imperfections. :)

Made with p5.js.
Primary split 5% with The Processing Foundation.

Keys
- 1: view 1000px png (Default)
- 2: download 2000px png
- 4: download 4000px png
- 8: download 8000px png
- s: save the image as PNG

When downloading higher resolution pngs, it might take several seconds to redraw the whole image. Download will start immediately after redrawing is completed. Please bear with the slow rendering.

metadata.name: Disintegrating #88
metadata.description:
Disintegrating is an animated, interactive piece which allows the user to change the colour and luminosity of the lines within the artwork using mouse movement.

Move the mouse around the screen to see the colour changing effects.

mouseclick will stop the animation at its current state
'spacebar' will restart the animation
'r' will reset and restart the animation
'f' will set the animation to no disintegration at the current colours

Disintegrating is my first piece which includes a Webgl shader integrated with p5.js coding.

metadata.name: Secunda #92
Lines of Solitude #24
metadata.description:
There is a mystery in the lifeline, where we walk and discover all alone. Some landscapes make we breath this solitude.
